        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 12:55AM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 1255 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from 25 miles east of Ridgeway to 12 miles
north of Biddle, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ridgeway, Alzada, Hammond, Albion, Boyes, Belle Creek and Capitol.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
